						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Zepper wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Without telling us what specific thing you're confused by, it's very difficult to make it clearer.<br /><br />I'm not even clear where you got &quot;Odd and even clocks&quot; from.</div><br /><br />OK, from the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/CPU" class="postlink">wiki</a>: &quot;Every cycle on 6502 is either a read or a write cycle&quot;. Well, 0, 2, 4, 6, 8 <strong>even</strong> CPU clock cycles; 1, 3, 5, 7, 9 <em>odd</em> CPU clock cycles.</div><br /><br />What the wiki page is meaning to say is that there are no bus-idle cycles.  On every single cycle, the bus will be asked to do a read or a write, but not necessarily alternating between the two.</div>

